<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-724] Improve junit test integration - log harness information</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-724</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently we have ad-hoc logging (log4j) of setup/teardown and test start/end. Without this information it&apos;s often difficult to determine&lt;br/&gt;
what&apos;s going on (major milestones) in the logs relative to the tests performed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In junit 4.x &quot;@Rule&quot; annotations have been added that allow this to be done much more easily. This patch will add this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In particular we can access the test name easily during setup/teardown and the test itself. Additionally we can log more information on&lt;br/&gt;
success/failure of each test.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
